The paper proposes a market mechanism for renewable power producers in power systems, which involves finding a Nash equilibrium among the strategic RPPs in congestion-constrained power networks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with the efficient and reliable operation of power systems, which involves control and optimization, suggesting that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY), Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE), and Electrical Engineering and Systems (cs.EE) sub-categories.
